{
  "texts": [
    "We imagine by providing individualised antibiotic switch estimations such a system could support patientcentric decisions and provide assurance on if switching could be appropriate or not in a given clinical context.",
    "Figure 1 shows an overview of this research.",
    "Data 8694 unique intensive care unit (ICU) stays, were extracted from the MIMIC dataset 21, 22, with 1,668 from eICU [22] [23] [24].",
    "10 clinical features were selected based on the UK antimicrobial IVOS criteria 14 (Supplementary Table. 1).",
    "Transformation of those temporally dynamic values into time series features as detailed in Section 4.1 resulted in 960 unique features for each day of each patient's stay."
  ]
}